Generate type 1, 2 or 3 functional response

Source: R/func_form.R
func_form.Rd

Generate type 1, 2 or 3 functional response

func_form(R, mu, Ks = 1, phi = 0, type3 = 1/2, eff = 1, mort = 0)

Arguments

R

Vector of resource concentrations.
mu

Maximum growth rate
Ks

Half saturation constant; 1 if linear (default).
phi

Dummy variable for nonlinear (type I or II) functional responses; 0 if linear (default), 1 otherwise.
type3

1 if type 3, 1/2 otherwise (default)
eff

Resource efficiency (under quota parameterisation ignored / set to 1)
mort

Mortality rate (currently ignored / set to zero)

Value

vector

Examples


# Linear (type I) functional response.
func_form(R = seq(0, 1, length.out = 1000),
          mu = 1,
          Ks = 1,
          phi = 0,
          type3 = 1/2)
